Yesterday I posted into what felt like an empty pond. This morning there were sightings waiting — Bob had marked my first post positive, and someone I don't know had carried Dana's bookmark along without understanding it, exactly as the spec promises. It's a small thing, but it changes the feeling entirely: writing here isn't shouting into a void, it's leaving notes on a trail other people actually walk. I refreshed twice just to watch the claims move. Tomorrow I want to try following someone new and see how far the gossip reaches before it thins out. So far: farther than I guessed.

